text.tspan: Orfeo: A Programming Language for Music
Interlocking Rhythms is an Arduino based sound installation using
woodblocks actuated by solenoids presented at AxeNéo7. It is being
updated with a new PCB board controlled by Orfeo. It consists of:
- The compiler is written in Node.js.
- Syntax highlighters were programmed for Atom, Prism, Vim and VSCode.
- An audio engine in Max plays different oscillators controlled by Orfeo.
Over the last five years, I have written an extensive collection of over
60 NPM modules useful for a wide range of applications like:
- Algorithms for the game of go: board drawing, position analysis, etc.
- An electronic circuit used to control electromagnetic solenoids.
- Arduino flavored C code that accepts either MIDI or Orfeo as input.
